  m_Name: StoryCard_02_CrookedPintle
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Hollowfen.Data.StoryCardData
  _id: crooked_pintle
  _act: Act I
  _scene: Scene 2
  _title: The Crooked Pintle
  _subtitle: Beside the village well, Old Bram returns the mill key.
  _body: "The well stands between them and the half-lit Pintle. Bram remembers Wren
    hiding beneath his bar while Marra worked the kitchen, and the old innkeeper
    looks smaller than memory allowed. He kept the mill key through three wet winters
    because her father asked him to. It is the one promise he can still place in
    Wren's hand."
  _wrenNote: Bram kept Dad's key and his promise. He used to be the loudest man in
    any room. Today every word sounded like something he had carried too long.
  _beats:
  - Bram welcomes Wren home and remembers her childhood at the Pintle.
  - The Wend changed course three winters ago and killed the mill wheel.
  - Wren takes the key and turns toward the long lane to the mill.
  _image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 6694bb06854ab4257b0e6387374d62db, type: 3}
  _unlockAt: 1
  _questId: speakBram
